<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1437,2041]" box="[151,1048,1437,1465]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1437,1464]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[304,412,1438,1464]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Holotype</typeStatus>
. Female. Body length 
<quantity box="[663,751,1438,1465]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
, fore wing length 
<quantity box="[955,1044,1438,1465]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1437,2041]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,268,1473,1500]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Head.</emphasis>
Transverse in dorsal view, 2.0× as wide as long, as wide as mesoscutum. Vertex between eye and posterior ocellus somewhat shiny with extremely shallow punctures. Temple rough, uneven with shallow punctures, slightly constricted. Face 0.8× as high as wide, shiny with superficial punctures, inner margin of eyes subparallelsided. Ocelli small, posterior tangent to anterior ocellus just touching posterior ocelli, distance between fore and hind ocellus slightly longer than diameter of hind ocellus, POL:OD:OOL=5.0:1.5:4.0. Antenna distinctly longer than body length, weakly closely articulated, penultimate flagellomere 2.4× longer than wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1437,2041]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,329,1691,1717]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Length:width:height = 40.0:25.5:25.5. Disc of mesonotum dull with tiny, dense, strong punctures, becoming shallower towards apex, interspaces not smaller than diameter of puncture, indistinctly rugulose between punctures at extremely posterior end of notaulic courses. Scutellar sulcus curved, narrow with dense carinae inside. Scutellum shiny and polished entirely, median length slightly longer than basal width. Lateral polished field of scutellum reaching half length of scutellum. Propodeum slightly shiny, long, areola V-shaped apically, without costulae, spiracle enclosed by hind keels, elsewhere shiny, polished. Mesopleuron shiny, anterior parts strongly and sparsely punctate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1437,2041]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,261,1943,1969]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Legs.</emphasis>
Hind femur relatively thin, 3.0× longer than wide. Hind coxa shiny with merely extremely shallow punctures above (basally). Spines on outer side of third tibia not dense. Inner spurs of hind tibia nearly half length of hind basitarsus, outer spur 1/3. Basitarsus of hind leg about as long as tarsomeres 2–4 combined, claws of normal size.
</paragraph>
