<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,153,1152]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,278,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Wings.</emphasis>
Pterostigma 3.0× as long as its widest part. Vein 1-R1 1.1× longer than pterostigma, 4.8× as long as its distance from apex of marginal cell. Vein r arising from middle of pterostigma, nearly perpendicular to the latter, 1.3× longer than width of pterostigma, 1.6× longer than 2-SR, indistinctly angled at junction, 2-M half as long as 2- SR, the latter as long as m-cu, 1-SR nearly as long as 2-SR+M and 2-M. First discal cell of fore wing weakly (1.1×) wider than high. Second submarginal cell of hind wing nearly as wide as high. Vein cu-a indistinctly curved. Hind wing not broad, length of 1-M indistinctly shorter than distance between its distal extremity and apex of vannal lobe, and vannal lobe beyond its widest part strongly curved and hairless.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,153,1152]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Metasoma.</emphasis>
Almost as long as mesosoma (42.0:40.0). T1 nearly parallel-sided, long, 1.8× longer than hind width, concave at basal two-fifths, turned-over part slightly shiny, weakly subrugose-punctate medially, smooth to slightly uneven at apical third, longitudinal channel absent, and apical tubercle polished. T2 shiny, smooth, 3.3× wider than long in the middle, nearly straight apically. T3 1.7× longer than T2. Tergites posterior to T2 shiny, smooth and pubescent. Hypopygium distinctly shorter than apex of metasoma. Ovipositor sheath as long as length of hind tibia, relatively narrow, hairs long and not dense, apical attenuation of ovipositor indistinct and long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,153,1152]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,285,620,647]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Colour.</emphasis>
Black. Tegula brown. Palpi pale yellow (except blackish basally) and spurs white. Antenna and ovipositor sheath dark brown. Labrum and mandible dark brown. Legs brown to black, except most parts of fore femur, fore tibia with tarsus, extreme apex of mid femur, mid tibia with tarsus, extreme apical part of hind tibia and apical two to three segments of hind tarsus pale yellow to weakly reddish yellow. Wing membrane hyaline, setae light brownish, C+SC+R, 1-R1, border of pterostigma, r, 2-SR and 2-M light yellowish brown, other alar veins more or less pale yellowish brownish, pterostigma more or less pale medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,153,1152]" box="[199,392,837,863]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,837,863]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
