<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,153,1152]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,945,971]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2020" box="[568,685,946,971]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Apanteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuator">
<emphasis box="[568,685,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">attenuator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” derives from the Latin, referring to the long apical attenuation of ovipositor.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,153,1152]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1017,1043]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wilkinson" authorityName="Wilkinson" authorityYear="1928" box="[671,969,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Apanteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="machaeralis">
<emphasis box="[671,842,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">A. machaeralis</emphasis>
Wilkinson
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in the following: penultimate flagellomere 2.4× longer than wide (one and a quarter in latter); metacarp 4.8× as long as its distance from apex of marginal cell (much shorter, 3.0× in latter); and anterior part of mesopleuron shiny, evenly punctate (rugose, without punctures in latter).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
